  "texts": [
    "In contrast, vipr, yields broader score distributions for both true foreground and background voxels.",
    "Despite this spread, the two distributions remain well separated, reflecting reliable discrimination.",
    "Importantly, voxels with high-confidence wrong classifications are rare, suggesting that vipr's confidence, even when dispersed, is generally well calibrated.The bottom panels present the distributions of predicted probabilities conditioned on the ground truth class, where for each voxel we use the probability that the network assigns to its actual class (one of the seven possible ones).",
    "Again, voxels are grouped into foreground and background.",
    "This representation directly reveals how confident the models are in making their predictions."
